Slash reminders are always private
Fixes a small bug where sending a slash command reminder in a server would consider it a public reminder because GuildID was set, and used as the discriminator.
This is remidied by checking if the message ID is null, which is indicative that the reminder was set from a slash command/modal, and thusly should always be considered private.
Commented on #1366 Cache threads upon thread creation
Experiment with allowing EF Core to track during update
Small update to how configs are updated

AddDiscordGateway supports mods now
(Omitting the additional call to AddDiscordRest also fixes an issue in which policies were added twice, thusly causing an issue with trying to add the token to the context)
